st\"||[[Xi'an]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u897f\u5b89}}||colspan=\"2\"|1949\u20131954\n|-bgcolor=#f5c3c4\n|[[Greater administrative area|Xinan]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u897f\u5357}}||{{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|X\u012bn\u00e1n}}||\"Southwest\"||[[Chongqing]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u91cd\u5e86}}||colspan=\"2\"|1949\u20131954\n|- style = \"background:#606060; height: 2pt\"\n|}\n\n====Provinces====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Name !! Hanzi !! [[Pinyin]] !! Abbreviation !! Capital !! Hanzi !! Note\n|-bgcolor=#f5c3c4\n|[[Andong Province|Andong]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u5b89\u4e1c}}||{{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|\u0100nd\u014dng}}||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u5b89}} {{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|\u0101n}}||[[Tonghua]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u901a\u5316}}||1949 abolished \u2192 Liaodong, Jilin\n|-\n|[[Anhui Province|Anhui]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u5b89\u5fbd}}||{{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|\u0100nhu\u012b}}||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u7696}} {{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|w\u01cen}}||[[Hefei]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u5408\u80a5}}||1949 abolished \u2192 Wanbei, Wannan; 1952 reverted\n|-bgcolor=#f5c3c4\n|[[Chahar Province|Chahar]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u5bdf\u54c8\u5c14}}||{{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|Ch\u00e1h\u0101'\u011br}}||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u5bdf}} {{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|ch\u00e1}}||[[Zhangjiakou]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u5f20\u5bb6\u53e3}}||1952 abolished \u2192 Inner Mongolia, Hebei\n|-bgcolor=lightblue\n|[[Fujian]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u798f\u5efa}}||{{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|F\u00faji\u00e0n}}||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u95fd}} {{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|m\u01d0n}}||[[Fuzhou]] (PRC)<br>[[Jincheng, Kinmen|Jincheng]] (ROC)||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u798f\u5dde}}||parts of the Fujian Province consisting of Kinmen and Matsu are retained by the ROC\n|-\n|[[Gansu]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u7518\u8083}}||{{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|G\u0101ns\u00f9}}||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u7518}} {{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|g\u0101n}}||[[Lanzhou]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u5170\u5dde}}|| 1958 Ningxia split into its own autonomous region\n|-\n|[[Guangdong]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u5e7f\u4e1c}}||{{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|Gu\u01cengd\u014dng}}||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u7ca4}} {{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin