iakou]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u5f20\u5bb6\u53e3}}||1952 abolished \u2192 Inner Mongolia, Hebei\n|-bgcolor=lightblue\n|[[Fujian]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u798f\u5efa}}||{{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|F\u00faji\u00e0n}}||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u95fd}} {{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|m\u01d0n}}||[[Fuzhou]] (PRC)<br>[[Jincheng, Kinmen|Jincheng]] (ROC)||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u798f\u5dde}}||parts of the Fujian Province consisting of Kinmen and Matsu are retained by the ROC\n|-\n|[[Gansu]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u7518\u8083}}||{{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|G\u0101ns\u00f9}}||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u7518}} {{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|g\u0101n}}||[[Lanzhou]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u5170\u5dde}}|| 1958 Ningxia split into its own autonomous region\n|-\n|[[Guangdong]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u5e7f\u4e1c}}||{{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|Gu\u01cengd\u014dng}}||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u7ca4}} {{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|yu\u00e8}}||[[Guangzhou]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u5e7f\u5dde}}||1952 & 1965 Fangchenggang, Qinzhou, Beihai \u2192 Guangxi; 1955 reverted<br>1988 Hainan split into its own province\n|-bgcolor=#f5c3c4\n|[[Guangxi]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u5e7f\u897f}}||{{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|Gu\u01cengx\u012b}}||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u6842}} {{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|gu\u00ec}}||[[Nanning]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u5357\u5b81}}||1958 province \u2192 autonomous region\n|-\n|[[Guizhou]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u8d35\u5dde}}||{{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|Gu\u00eczh\u014du}}||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u9ed4}} {{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|qi\u00e1n}}||[[Guiyang]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u8d35\u9633}}||\n|-\n|[[Hainan]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u6d77\u5357}}||{{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|H\u01cein\u00e1n}}||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u743c}} {{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|qi\u00f3ng}}||[[Haikou]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u6d77\u53e3}}||\n|-\n|[[Hebei]]||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u6cb3\u5317}}||{{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|H\u00e9b\u011bi}}||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u5180}} {{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|j\u00ec}}||{{nowrap|[[Baoding]] (1949\u201354; 1967\u201368)}}<br>[[Tianjin]] (1954\u201367)<br>[[Shijiazhuang]] (present)||{{lang|zh-Hans|\u4fdd\u5b9a<br>\u5929\u6d25<br>\u77f3\u5bb6\u5e84}}||1967 Tianjin split into its own municipality